{"lemma":"كَسْبُ","slug":"كَسْبُ","root":"ك.س.ب","root_slug":"ك-س-ب","root_link":"/words/roots/ك-س-ب","pos":"N","pos_camel":"noun","paradigm":[],"frequency_in_corpus":0,"cross_references":{"qac":{"found":true,"lemma_key":"كَسْبُ","root":"كسب","pos":"V","occurrence_count":62},"wiktextract":{"found":true,"entry_count":4,"pos_tags":["noun","verb"],"has_etymology":false,"sense_count":7},"lanes":{"found":true,"entry_ids":["n36926","n36927","n36928"],"search_url":"https://lanelexicon.com/?s=%D9%83%D9%8E%D8%B3%D9%92%D8%A8%D9%8F"}},"translations":null,"definition":{"source":"wiktextract","senses":[{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to win (a struggle or war)"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to earn, to gain, to try to earn a living"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to gather riches, knowledge"},{"pos":"verb","gloss":"to make someone gain, let someone share the profit"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"verbal noun of كَسَبَ (kasaba) (form I)","tags":["form-of","noun-from-verb"]},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"revenue"},{"pos":"noun","gloss":"alternative form of كُسْبَة (kusba, “refuse of oil seeds”)","tags":["alt-of","alternative"]}]},"etymology":null,"ipa":null,"lanes_definition":{"source":"lanes","entries":[{"entry_id":"n36926","headword_ar":"كَسَبَ","root":"ksb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":", aor."},{"kind":"text","text":", inf. n."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasobN","text_ar":"كَسْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, Msb) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kisobN","text_ar":"كِسْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He collected"},{"kind":"text","text":"(wealth &c.]; (S,"},{"kind":"page_break","n":2609},{"kind":"text","text":"K;) as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktsbhu","text_ar":"اكتسبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (S.) This is the original signification. (S.) ―         -b2-  [Hence,]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gained, acquired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"wealth or the like; as also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktsb","text_ar":"اكتسب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasabotu $ayoy^FA","text_ar":"كَسَبْتُ شَيْيًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Akotasabotuhu","text_ar":"اكْتَسَبْتُهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"are syn., [signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I gained a thing"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (S.) ―         -b3-  Hence [also],"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasaba","text_ar":"كَسَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktsb","text_ar":"اكتسب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K, Msb) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tks~b","text_ar":"تكسّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"(K)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He sought, sought after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sought to gain, sustenance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K,) for his family: (Msb:) or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasaba","text_ar":"كَسَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he got,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obtained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gained, acquired,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sustenance,"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.]; and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktsb","text_ar":"اكتسب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":","},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he applied himself with art and diligence"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"to get,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"obtain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gain, acquire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earn, sustenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c.;"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he laboured to earn,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gain, sustenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: (Sb, K:) [so] also ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tks~b","text_ar":"تكسّب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"is explained by"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"takal~afa Alkasoba","text_ar":"تَكَلَّفَ الكَسْبَ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he applied himself, as to a task, to gain, &c."},{"kind":"text","text":"(S.) ―         -b4-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasaba","text_ar":"كَسَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"is also said to signify, and originally, both"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he sought,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sought after,"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"sustenance"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; and"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he laboured in seeking,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"seeking after, sustenance."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA.) ―         -b5-  ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktsb","text_ar":"اكتسب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"has a more intensive signification than"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasaba","text_ar":"كَسَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; and hence, in the last verse of the second chap. of the Kur ["},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"lahaA maA kasabato waEalayohaA maA A@kotasabato","text_ar":"لَهَا مَا كَسَبَتْ وَعَلَيْهَا مَا ا@كْتَسَبَتْ"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"To it"},{"kind":"text","text":"shall be given"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what"},{"kind":"text","text":"reward"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"it hath earned, and upon it"},{"kind":"text","text":"shall be executed"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"what punishment it hath drawn upon itself"},{"kind":"text","text":"], the latter is used with reference to what is good; and the former, with reference to what is evil. (IJ.) You say,"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasaba xayorFA","text_ar":"كَسَبَ خَيْرًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did, good"},{"kind":"text","text":"]: and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktsb","text_ar":"اكتسب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"$ar~FA","text_ar":"شَرًّا"},{"kind":"text","text":"(tropical:)  ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He gained,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"did, evil"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. (A.) ―         -b6-  [This distinction, however, is not always observed: for]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasaba","text_ar":"كَسَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies,"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He did"},{"kind":"text","text":"either a good or an evil deed: [because he who does so earns, or draws upon himself, reward or punishment.] (Jel in ii. 281; and iii. 24; &c.) And ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktsb","text_ar":"اكتسب","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He committed"},{"kind":"text","text":"an act of which he was accusable. (Jel in xxxiii. 58.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasaba A_ivomFA","text_ar":"كَسَبَ اـِثْمًا"},{"kind":"text","text":"and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aktsbhu","text_ar":"اكتسبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":"signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"committed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or]"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"burdened himself with"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"taHam~ala","text_ar":"تَحَمَّلَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"),"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a sin,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"crime."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) ―         -b7-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasabahu maAlFA","text_ar":"كَسَبَهُ مَالًا"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"mAlA","text_ar":"مالا"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aksbhu","text_ar":"اكسبهُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IAar, IAth, K,) but the former is the more approved: the latter is by Fr and some others rejected: (TA:)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He caused him to gain, acquire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earn, wealth:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth, Msb:) or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"he assisted him to gain, acquire,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earn, wealth."},{"kind":"text","text":"(IAth.)"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"ksbhu","text_ar":"كسبهُ"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"EilomFA","text_ar":"عِلْمًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He caused him to gain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"acquire, knowledge."},{"kind":"text","text":"(Msb.) [In like manner,]"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"AlEaboda","text_ar":"العَبْدَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Asotakosabotu","text_ar":"اسْتَكْسَبْتُ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"I caused the slave to gain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"make gain;"},{"kind":"text","text":"the verb having here the sense of the measure"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^afoEalotuhu","text_ar":"اَفْعَلْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"; like as"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Aisotaxorajotuhu","text_ar":"اِسْتَخْرَجْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"signifies"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^axorajotuhu","text_ar":"اَخْرَجْتُهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":". (Msb.) [See an ex. voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^adiymN","text_ar":"اَدِيمٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":".] ―         -b8-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"nahaY Eano kasobi AlA_imaA'i","text_ar":"نَهَى عَنْ كَسْبِ الاـِمَاءِ"},{"kind":"text","text":"["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"He"},{"kind":"text","text":"(Mohammad)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"forbade the making female slaves to earn money,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like,"},{"kind":"text","text":"("},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"by prostitution"},{"kind":"text","text":")]. (TA, from a trad.) ―         -b9-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"maA kasaba","text_ar":"مَا كَسَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":"in the Kur cxi, 2, is said to signify"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"His children."},{"kind":"text","text":"A man's children are among the things termed his"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasob","text_ar":"كَسْب"},{"kind":"text","text":". (TA.) ―         -b10-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasabahu EajabFA","text_ar":"كَسَبَهُ عَجَبًا"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"It occasioned,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"caused, him to wonder."},{"kind":"text","text":"(TA, voce"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"A^aEojaba","text_ar":"اَعْجَبَ"},{"kind":"text","text":".)"}],"source_refs":["S","K","Msb","Sb","IAar","IAth","TA"]},{"entry_id":"n36927","headword_ar":"كَسْبٌ","root":"ksb","body":[{"kind":"text","text":"inf. n. of 1. q. v. ―         -b2-"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"fulaAnN Tay~ibu Alkasobi","text_ar":"فُلَانٌ طَيِّبُ الكَسْبِ"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almakosabi","text_ar":"المَكْسَبِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almakosibi","text_ar":"المَكْسِبِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Almakosibapi","text_ar":"المَكْسِبَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkisobapi","text_ar":"الكِسْبَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (S, K,) and ↓"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"Alkasiybapi","text_ar":"الكَسِيبَةِ","orth_type":"arrow"},{"kind":"text","text":", (IM,) ["},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"Such a one makes good gain:"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kasobN","text_ar":"كَسْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":"&c. signifying"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"gain, acquisition,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"earning:"},{"kind":"text","text":"and also"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"a deed,"},{"kind":"text","text":"whether good or evil]."}],"source_refs":["S","K","IM"]},{"entry_id":"n36928","headword_ar":"كُسْبٌ","root":"ksb","body":[{"kind":"italic_en","text":"i. q."},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kunjArq","text_ar":"كُنجارق"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kanojaArahu","text_ar":"كَنْجَارَهُ"},{"kind":"text","text":"], a Persian word, called by some of the people of Es-Sawád"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusobaj","text_ar":"كُسْبَج"},{"kind":"text","text":"[or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusobah","text_ar":"كُسْبَه"},{"kind":"text","text":"; i. e., The"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dregs of sesamegrain,"},{"kind":"text","text":"or"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"the like, from which the oil has been expressed"},{"kind":"text","text":"]; (TA;)"},{"kind":"italic_en","text":"dregs remaining after the expression of oil:"},{"kind":"text","text":"(S, K:) [as also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kuzobN","text_ar":"كُزْبٌ"},{"kind":"text","text":":] from the Persian"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"k$b","text_ar":"كشب"},{"kind":"text","text":", (AM,) [or rather"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusobah","text_ar":"كُسْبَه"},{"kind":"text","text":", or"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"kusobaj","text_ar":"كُسْبَج"},{"kind":"text","text":"]. See also"},{"kind":"arabic","text_bw":"tax~N","text_ar":"تَخٌّ"},{"kind":"text","text":"."}],"source_refs":["S","K","AM"]}]}}